The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared the candidate of the All Progressive Congress (APC), Dr. John Kayode Fayemi, winner of the Ekiti state governorship election held yesterday in the state. Fayemi won the election with a total vote of 197,459 while the leading contender and candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Prof. Kolapo Olusola Eleka had 178,121 votes. The People For Democratic Change (PDC)’s candidate came third with a total vote of 1,242. INEC’s Chief Returning Officer for the Ekiti state governorship election, Prof. Abel Idowu Olayinka, who is also the Vice Chancellor of the University of Ibadan, said: “That John Olukayode Fayemi of the APC, having satisfied the requirements of the law and got the highest number of votes is hereby declared winner and returned elected.” While announcing few minutes to 8am on Sunday, he gave the figures as follows: Accredited Number of Voters – 405,861 Lawful votes Accord – 250 AA – 41 ACD – 1,149 AD – 216 ADP – 1,082 AGA - 107 AGAP – 31 ANRP – 125 APA – 1,199 APC – 197,459 APDA – 464 APGA – 70 BNPP – 14 DA – 14 DPC – 147 DPP – 181 FJP – 42 GPN – 20 ID – 212 KOWA – 23 LP – 280 MMN – 35 MPN – 231 NDMP – 84 NPC – 353 PANDEL - 74 PDC – 1,242 PDP – 178,121 PPA – 632 PPN – 107 SDP – 367 UDP – 29 UPN – 33 YDP – 31 YPP – 49 Total Valid Votes – 384,594 Rejected Votes -   18,857 TOTAL VOTES CAST - 403,451